ca.utoronto.utm.assignment1.othello

Class OthelloControllerRandomVSRandom

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.utoronto.utm.assignment1.othello.OthelloControllerRandomVSRandom

  • public class OthelloControllerRandomVSRandom
extends java.lang.Object
    Determine whether the first player or second player has the advantage when both are playing a Random Strategy. Do this by creating two players which use a random strategy and have them play each other for 10000 games. What is your conclusion, does the first or second player have some advantage, at least for a random strategy? State the null hypothesis H0, the alternate hypothesis Ha and about which your experimental results support. Place your short report in randomVsRandomReport.txt.
    Author:
    arnold
